                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6211/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-23T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 23, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 23—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>461. Ribbentrop arrived promptly at 1:00 by air and was met at the airport on
                    behalf of the Soviet Government by Potemkin, the Commander of the Moscow
                    garrison, and other Soviet officials. He was to see Molotov at 3 o’clock this
                    afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
